    old "“I mean, there’s {i}a{/i} story, but not a good one.” He clears his throat. “For years I wanted to have an inn called {i}Pelt{/i}, but in my city it would be in bad taste. Taverns and inns named with a single word were cheap, had a nasty reputation. There was the {i}Claw{/i}, and {i}Mugger{/i}, {i}Basilisk{/i}, and {i}Blissful{/i}, I think. The {i}good{/i} places used at least two words. {i}Empty Barrel{/i}, {i}A Rose and a Helmet{/i}, {i}Empress’ Smile{/i}. {i}Pig Head{/i} was the exception, it was a real dive,” he chuckles. \n\n“In my soul it’s still just a {color=#f6d6bd}Pelt{/color}. Pelts are what we came here for, and what will make us reach our goals.” "
