    old "“Let me think...{color=#f6d6bd}Thais’{/color} husband? I’ve barely talked to him, ever. He stays inside, cooking. And spends a lot of time with their children, or in the garden. I admire people who take care of orphans, especially if they treat them like their own, not just as a free hand to plow the field.” He tilts his head to the right and frowns gently. “But I also don’t think he’s much of an innkeeper.” "
